<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id9153998c-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s10261"><num value="10261">§ 10261.</num><heading> Sanctions exception relating to importation of goods</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id9153998d-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s10261/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> In general</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The authorities and requirements to impose sanctions under this chapter shall not include the authority or requirement to impose sanctions on the importation of goods.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id9153998e-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s10261/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Good defined</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In this section, the term “good” means any article, natural or man-made substance, material, supply, or manufactured product, including inspection and test equipment, and excluding technical data.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id9153998f-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6">(<ref href="/us/pl/117/263/dE/tLV/s5579">Pub. L. 117–263, div. E, title LV, § 5579</ref>, <date date="2022-12-23">Dec. 23, 2022</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/136/3370">136 Stat. 3370</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
